    <div class="body">
      <div class="quotetitle"><a href="http://arstechnica.com/information-technology/2014/03/bank-that-claimed-to-solve-bitcoins-security-problem-robbed-shuts-down/?comments=1&amp;post=26360005" class="postlink" rel="nofollow">Ulf</a> wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">People whine and whine and whine about regulations, but there's a reason why they exist.</div><br>Truth.<br><br>It's downright hilarious watching Bitcoin users discovering for themselves just why even the relatively weak regulations we have on "regular" banking is so valuable.
      
