    <span class="author" data-post-author="dmsilev"><a href="http://arstechnica.com/civis/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=221498&amp;sid=e048854bc138e565d18581a2d2516ebd">dmsilev</a></span><span class="rank">Ars Scholae Palatinae</span>
      <aside class="icons">
        
        <a href="http://arstechnica.com/information-technology/2014/03/bank-that-claimed-to-solve-bitcoins-security-problem-robbed-shuts-down/?comments=1&post=26360217#comment-26360217" title="2014-03-04T09:51:05-06:00" class="timeago datetime">Tue Mar 04, 2014 9:51 am</a>
        
          <span class="highlight reader-fav">Reader Fav</span>
        
        <span class="hidden-icon-start"></span>
        
      </aside>
    </header>
    <div class="body">
      As far as I can tell, there are three reasons why people use Bitcoins:<br />1) Philosophical reasons. Wanting a distributed currency independent of central banks, desire for anonymity, etc.<br />2) Wanting to purchase ...alternative goods. <br />3) Investment/speculation<br /><br />The people in group (1) are finding out good and hard just why things like the FDIC exist.
      
    </div>
