      <aside class="icons">
        
        <a href="http://arstechnica.com/information-technology/2014/03/bank-that-claimed-to-solve-bitcoins-security-problem-robbed-shuts-down/?comments=1&post=26360517#comment-26360517" title="2014-03-04T10:15:39-06:00" class="timeago datetime">Tue Mar 04, 2014 10:15 am</a>
        
        <span class="hidden-icon-start"></span>
        
      </aside>
    </header>
    <div class="body">
      <div class="quotetitle"><a href="http://arstechnica.com/civis/viewtopic.php?p=26360347#p26360347" class="postlink" rel="nofollow">edzieba</a> wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">As always, the only ay to guarantee security of your bitcoins is in a REGULATED bank (of which none yet exist until at least one country pulls their finger out and actually gets some legislation in order), or offlie on youer own hardware. The same way that you can only secure cash in your own wallet in a safe, or in a regulate bank (i.e. not in your mate's mattress).<br /><br />That's the peril of Bircoin: you trade absolute control over your money with having to bear absolute responsibility for it. There's a lot of work that goes into managing money that you never see when you open a bank account, and that all becomes your job to handle. If you are happy managing your own pension, savings, investments etc, as well as having the skills of managing and securing your own server, then bitcoin is probably a good fit for you. If not, then buying some nebulous chunks of the blockchain and pointing them at a third party in the hope that at some point in the future you might be able to get them to point them back at you is not a winning move.</div><br /><br />You have no more control over your Bitcoins than you do over any other money in your wallet.
      
    </div>
    <footer>
      <aside class="vote">
        
        <a href="http://arstechnica.com/civis/ucp.php?mode=login&amp;return_to=http%3A%2F%2Farstechnica.com%2Finformation-technology%2F2014%2F03%2Fbank-that-claimed-to-solve-bitcoins-security-problem-robbed-shuts-down%2F%3Fcomments%3D1%26amp%3Bstart%3D0%23comment-26360517" class="vote_login vote_up_login" title="Login to vote up">up</a>
